briefdescription.para: Check whether modification event me is failed, and forward failure.

detaileddescription.para: To be used inside the propagate member function of a propagator or the commit member function of a brancher.

memberdef.name: GECODE_ME_CHECK_MODIFIED
memberdef.initializer: do { \ ModEvent __me__ ## __LINE__ = (me); \ if (::Gecode::me_failed(__me__ ## __LINE__)) \ return ::Gecode::ES_FAILED; \ modified |= ::Gecode::me_modified(__me__ ## __LINE__); \ } while (0)

briefdescription.para: Check whether execution status es is failed or subsumed, and forward failure or subsumption.
Check whether execution status es is failed, and fail space home.

memberdef.name: GECODE_REWRITE
memberdef.initializer: do { \ Propagator& __p__ ## __LINE__ = (prop); \ size_t __s__ ## __LINE__ = __p__ ## __LINE__.dispose(home); \ ExecStatus __es__ ## __LINE__ = (post); \ if (__es__ ## __LINE__ != ::Gecode::ES_OK) \ return ::Gecode::ES_FAILED; \ return home.ES_SUBSUMED_DISPOSED(__p__ ## __LINE__,__s__ ## __LINE__); \ } while (0)
